1
00:00:12,155 --> 00:00:15,578
Can you talk a little bit about modular classrooms?

2
00:00:15,678 --> 00:00:15,979
Sure.

3
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:30,953
So the modular classrooms in this particular option are going to be required in any scenario moving forward because we're moving around the entirety of the building and we're reconstructing it piece by pieces in a variety of phases as we go through.

4
00:00:31,093 --> 00:00:35,217
So when we touch in particular the C wing or the B wing,

5
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:39,484
We're impacting a tremendous number of classes in either one of those wings.

6
00:00:39,684 --> 00:00:43,828
The C wing has about, I think, 51 classrooms in it.

7
00:00:44,208 --> 00:00:46,430
The B wing may have about 45 classrooms in it.

8
00:00:46,550 --> 00:00:59,642
And so if we think about each one of those being an individual phase, at that time that we're actually touching either of those wings, we actually have to have a modular classroom building on the site somewhere to accommodate those 51 classrooms, potentially.

9
00:01:01,715 --> 00:01:19,860
Where exactly those modular classroom buildings might be located, we don't know that yet, but we'll look at various opportunities as compared to where parking needs to be, as compared to where construction, logistic, lay down areas need to be and try to find sort of that correct balance in terms of where.

10
00:01:20,960 --> 00:01:26,742
But the number of classrooms that we have to accommodate in the modular classroom buildings is considerable.

11
00:01:27,642 --> 00:01:38,905
Here, we don't have a lot of opportunities to reduce that overall, with the exception of thinking about the schedule for the school once we get into the construction process.

12
00:01:39,685 --> 00:01:53,988
And when I say by looking at the schedule from a classroom perspective, I'm really thinking about are there ways that we can shift towards a shared classroom model that might get better operational efficiencies and require a smaller number of classrooms

13
00:01:54,849 --> 00:02:08,042
Not in the finished condition, which we have to comply with, but even in the interim condition so that we don't have to build more temporary classroom spaces and displace more teachers and students into those temporary modular classrooms as part of the process.

14
00:02:08,322 --> 00:02:08,643
Sure.

15
00:02:09,043 --> 00:02:15,169
The other thing that I feel like I am thinking about when I'm thinking about modular classrooms in this option is that

16
00:02:17,130 --> 00:02:30,313
It doesn't look to me, and please tell us if this is not true, that there would be a way to avoid modular classrooms for RCT programs or some disruption of where they are because we would be renovating their space too, right?

17
00:02:30,533 --> 00:02:30,833
Correct.

18
00:02:30,893 --> 00:02:31,994
So there's disruption.

19
00:02:32,474 --> 00:02:39,816
When we talk about disruption, we don't want any students to be disrupted, but we know that every student will be disrupted through this process somehow or some way, right?

20
00:02:40,276 --> 00:02:43,696
But it's especially problematic in RCT spaces.

21
00:02:43,736 --> 00:02:45,857
So can you talk a little bit about your experience there?

22
00:02:46,297 --> 00:02:53,744
Yes, so the impact on the CTE students definitely needs to be considered alongside the academic students.

23
00:02:53,864 --> 00:02:55,525
It's a different type of consideration.

24
00:02:55,926 --> 00:03:04,493
There are some CTE programs where we could plan to have like a double-size modular classroom area where they could actually move out into that space.

25
00:03:04,533 --> 00:03:09,878
Something like a programming and web development where it's essentially a computer lab in terms of where they're going to be working.

26
00:03:10,398 --> 00:03:12,600
There are other programs, CTE programs like

27
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:21,148
auto tech, right, where it's difficult or impossible to build a temporary modular auto garage for them to work in.

28
00:03:21,228 --> 00:03:36,902
So what we've done in past projects where we have this type of situation and it's not feasible to rebuild temporary space is actually look to outside community partners that may have an available auto garage that the students could use to actually

29
00:03:38,245 --> 00:03:45,112
perform sort of the education, the curriculum instruction that they need in a remote facility.

30
00:03:45,553 --> 00:03:52,060
The downside there is that means that those students are hopping on a bus at the beginning of the day if it's a week on week off program.

31
00:03:52,693 --> 00:03:58,198
they're headed over to that shop the entirety that they're not on campus for any of the time when they should be.

32
00:03:59,059 --> 00:04:13,693
In some cases, if it is a week on week off program that may not look too different for them, but if it is a program where they are here in the morning and then they're moving into their CTE shops in the afternoon, it means that every day that they are hopping on a bus back and forth.

33
00:04:14,353 --> 00:04:24,587
So it's time lost on education and it's also taking them out of their educational environment, away from their peers, and away from all the resources that would otherwise be here at the high school.

34
00:04:24,627 --> 00:04:29,995
So very, very impactful in terms of what it would mean to those CT students.

35
00:04:30,817 --> 00:04:38,702
So when we talk about modulars and disruption, I think many of these options have disruption and modulars.

36
00:04:40,943 --> 00:04:53,910
As we went through them and made these decisions to advance these six, this felt like the most problematic to me in terms of modulars and disruption, and particularly disruption of CTE spaces.

37
00:04:54,031 --> 00:04:54,591
Is that fair?

38
00:04:55,191 --> 00:05:18,607
It is fair to say because we just don't have the lever and we'll talk about that when we're talking about some of the C and the D options in terms of potentially opening a portion of the building earlier in phased construction so that we could move students and teachers into new construction as opposed to a temporary modular which is when if we have the option of building something new off the footprint of the existing building we do have that available to us.

39
00:05:19,007 --> 00:05:24,371
The B 1.2 option does not have that available because we're sticking within the existing footprint and we're going up so

40
00:05:24,631 --> 00:05:27,719
There's nowhere to go but here, essentially, in terms of space.

